Eagle-Headed Genie Between Two Sacred Trees. 
Each genie depicted in the reliefs exhibited here carries two knives tucked in his garment and in some cases a whetstone for sharpening the blades as well. Knives of this type are known to have been used from as early as the twelfth century b.c. Their hilts were often inlaid with bone, ivory, bronze, or precious metal, and their scabbards were decorated with the heads of birds. The whetstones were also decorated with an animal head, often of a horse or a bull.
CULTURES Assyrian; Ancient Near Eastern
MEDIUM Alabaster
Place Made: Nimrud, Assyria (Iraq). 
DATES ca. 883-859 B.C.E.
PERIOD Neo-Assyrian Period
DIMENSIONS 84 13/16 x 83 1/8 in. (215.5 x 211.2 cm)
Brooklyn Museum

The Sajama Lines in western Bolivia are a network of tens of thousands of perfectly straight tracks drawn on the ground with continuous lines that were carved perfectly straight across hills and mountains without any devation.
_

The drawings allegedly began more than 3000 years ago with the indigenous peoples of South America who live near the Sajama glacier, located 300km from Tiwanaku and Puma Punku. 
_

They look like roads, about 3 meters wide, stripped of all vegetation. Many lines run to hilltops and up the highest mountains, whose peaks are impossible to climb even today. 
_

The area around Sajama is so cold and the frost is so thick that the hardy quinoa or barley (which even grows upon the Alps) don't grow there, and the grass and fruitless plants that were dug out didn't grow back over the millennia, which is quite an enigma because the volcanic soil was only slightly disturbed by the digging.
_

It would have required an unimaginable amount of work to dig out all the deep-rooted needle grass and t’ola plants without steel tools, millions of people and hours of labor in the frost. 
_

Being so similar to the Nazca lines, many claim that they might've been drawn by the same civilization that left the geoglyphs in Perù. 
_

Research has revealed that this network of lines covers an area of 22,525 square km, 15 times larger than that covered by the Nazca lines, making it the largest archaeological site in the Andes, with an estimated length of 16,000 km, about 3 times the width of the United States of America. 
_

Researchers at the University of Pennsylvania, when describing the lines, declared:

“Although many of these lines extend over 20km (and possibly more), they appear to have been drawn with incredible precision, despite the hostile topography and natural obstacles. The total number of lines is difficult to perceive from ground level, but from the air or from the top of a hill they are impressive.”
_

Most of the pictures come from Google Earth, including a mysterious circle drawn on the slopes of a mountain (Pic.9).

Every once in a while archaeologists (and sometimes amateur archaeologists) make remarkable discoveries. Sometimes, the finding is so surprising that they are unable to explain what it is they've found, how it came into existence, or ascertain its value. Here are 4 unexplained artifacts that many believe should have never existed, or for which we have no satisfying explanation.
1. Ubaid Lizard Figurines
The discovery at the Al Ubaid archaeological site, where many pre-Sumerian 7,000-year-old artifacts were found, depict humanoid figures with lizard-like characteristics. Now interested parties are left wondering whether these are images of mythical figures or actual beings who still live among us. The figurines are presented with long heads, almond shaped eyes, long tapered faces and a lizard-type nose. What exactly they represent is completely unknown.
2. The Antikythera mechanism – a Greek ancient computer
The Antikythera mechanism has been labeled the first mechanical computer. Found in a shipwreck off the Greek island of Antikythera, buried under 45 meters of water it was designed to calculate astronomical positions.
3. The Dropa Stones
Similar to phonograph records — nine inches in diameter, a circle cut into their centers and an obvious spiral groove. This artifact id believed to be more than 10,000 years old. But the spiral, as it turns out, is composed of tiny hieroglyphics. When studied and translated, it was revealed that the discs tell the amazing story of spaceships that crashed into the mountains, piloted by people who called themselves the Dropa.
4. The London hammer – a tool older than history
The rock encasing this hammer was dated to the Ordovician – more than 400 million years ago! The hammer’s head, made of more than 96% iron, is far more pure than anything nature could have achieved without an assist from technology...
